DC Advisory Partners , formerly known
as Close Brothers Corporate Finance, hired Sergio Ronga as a
managing director in its debt group.  Ronga moves from  Macquarie Group Ltd. (MQG) , where he was a
managing director in the debt advisory team, London-based DC
Advisory said in an e-mailed statement today. He will advise
clients in the infrastructure and social service sectors working
alongside managing directors Jonathan Trower and Ciara Oâ€™Neill,
according to the statement.  DC Advisory was formed when Japanese securities firm  Daiwa
Securities Group Inc. (8601)  bought the corporate finance division of
European investment bank Close Brothers Group Plc in May 2009.  To contact the reporter on this story:
